48th lvl Ranjuh/Wizard pet
(aka da GI...)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/bthesentinent.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=monarch>Monarch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Member</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/01 12:47:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Dumbfounded in Southern Karana, need some advice..</span><hr size=1> See, it's situations like this that makes me really not want to hunt with anyone unless Ive known them for a long time or belong to the same guild.  That's why most of the time I look for guild members to do any serious hunting with.<br>
<br>
Im not sure how I would react if something like this happend to me.  Probably really negitively.  So I try not to put myself in that sort of situation.<br>
<br>
<br>
Monarch, Frustrated 33rd Lvl Enchanter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/bthesentinent.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=teynorsax>Teynor Sax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Officer</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/01 1:33:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Dumbfounded in Southern Karana, need some advice..</span><hr size=1> Well, just to let you know what happened, Deseray did petition, and a GM showed up at the treant camp.  AFTER the group had split of course, it was just she and I there trying to hold it at the time..hehe.  Anyway, the GM talked to everyone who had been in the group that was still on, then just left, and Deseray didn't get crap.<br>
<br>
Now I too have grouped with Deseray and Lin in the past, and both seemed pretty nice to me.  I gotta' say though, Des handled it really badly.  Just after Shoumai left, she starts /ooc and /shout'ing to the zone that Lin is a bad, greedy person who should not be grouped with, and she's spamming the group.  Finally our cleric said she couldn't take the arguing anymore and left, as did the 'chanter and Eberheardt (who, by the way, still has the Cloak I believe).<br>
<br>
Anyway, she ended up getting nothing and will probably have a hard time getting groups in that zone now....gotta' love good ole' EverCamp.  :-)<br>
<br>
Tey <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ushoumai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shoumai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Member</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/01 5:16:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Thanks for the perspectives</span><hr size=1> Man, thats harsh.  Really disappointing in a big way, you always assume Justice will be served, or I do at least.  I am really naive(sp?),and when bad crap like that happens I am usually flabergasted by the whole situation.  I reckon is does just happen sometimes, really sad though and its hard to say if I would trust the others again to group with (I plan on hitting 30 or so with them bad trees!).  It goes go to show how much better Guild Groups are than pickups, I agree with what Hal said in the meeting...these Gob Mines Groups we had were awesome, most fun I have since Najena I think and that was again a Guild Thang hehe.  Oh and Elizae in Lake of Ill Omen at the windmill rocked too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   .  Anyway, thanks again...I'm rambling hehe.<br>
